======================================================================
PART 3: Parity structure of a1 and a2
======================================================================

  (a1 mod 2, a2 mod 2) distribution:
    (0, 0): 1115
    (0, 1): 550
    (1, 0): 902
    (1, 1): 433

  k = a1 + 2*a2 mod 2 = a1 mod 2 (since 2*a2 is even)
  So k is odd iff a1 is odd, k is even iff a1 is even.

